        <mxCell id="36OamRU7qbAxRdqJdja1-185" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. No matter what functtion code is, these 4 bytes always exist in the packet&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2. In the reading request, these 4 bytes fields should be 0x00&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. If exception happens, thiese 4 byte fields should be 0x00&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Data with network order:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;Host order U8 Parameter&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;= 0x11&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;--&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp; network order&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;byte 3 = 0x00, byte 2 = 0x00, byte 1 = 0x00, byte 0 = 0x11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Host order U32 Parameter = 0x12345678&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;--&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp; network order&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;byte 3 = 0x12, byte 2 = 0x34, byte 1 = 0x56, byte 0 = 0x78&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="shape=partialRectangle;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;connectable=0;strokeColor=inherit;overflow=hidden;fillColor=none;top=0;left=0;bottom=0;right=0;pointerEvents=1;fontSize=16;rowspan=1;colspan=4;align=left;" parent="36OamRU7qbAxRdqJdja1-177" vertex="1">
